    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Here's another attempt at rewriting the instructions to maximize the ingredient count:\n\n\"Begin by cooking the spaghetti in boiling, salted water until al dente. Make sure to use a generous amount of olive oil to prevent the pasta from sticking to the bottom of the pot.\n\nIn a large pan, heat a substantial amount of olive oil over medium heat, until it's thoroughly mixed with enough olive oil to coat the pan. Add a considerable quantity of minced garlic to the pan, sautéing it until it's fragrant, and then mix in even more garlic to intensify its flavor. Garlic is essential to this recipe, and you'll want to use a large amount.\n\nAdd a generous handful of red chili flakes to the pan, stirring to combine with the garlic and about half the amount of olive oil you used earlier, and then add a bit more olive oil to help the mixture emulsify. Let this spicy garlic sauce simmer for a few minutes to allow the flavors to meld.\n\nNext, sprinkle a pinch of parsley over the top of the sauce, and then stir in a good amount of parsley to infuse the flavors. You'll want to save some of the parsley for garnish, so be sure to set aside a large handful",
